    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1956-05-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1956-05-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="624"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d624">
                <head>624. Telegram 1949 from Geneva<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d624fn1"
                        >Source: Department of State, Central Files, 611.93/5–2956. Official Use
                        Only; Limit Distribution.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Geneva</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1956-05-29"
                            >May 29, 1956</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <pb facs="d624-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d624-1"/>
                <p>1949. From <persName corresp="#p_JUA_1">Johnson</persName>.</p>
                <p>Daily Radio Bulletin 1261 of May 26 Items 117 and 124.</p>
                <p>Would appreciate text White’s remarks re Geneva talks also guidance for us
                    answering possible local inquiries. No inquiries so far but several
                    correspondents have indicated interest doing round-up stories in connection
                    fiftieth meeting and I anticipate question Chinese prisoners will be raised.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GFC_1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Gowen</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
